abstract: American swimmer Haley Anderson wins five-kilometer open-water race at FINA world swimming championships in Kazan, Russia; other swimming results noted.
lead_paragraph: Fighting off windy and choppy conditions, Haley Anderson of the United States defended her title in the five-kilometer open-water race to claim the first medal of the FINA world swimming championships.
